Introduction

Jongho is a South Korean singer, dancer, songwriter, and actor under KQ Entertainment. He is a member of the boy group ATEEZ, in which he debuted on October 24, 2018 with the release of their first mini album "TREASURE EP.1: All to Zero".

Before debuting, Jongho participated in the survival show "MIXNINE" where he was eliminated after ranking 43rd.

In 2021, Jongho debuted as an actor through the KBS Drama 'Imitation', in which he played the supporting role of Hyuk, a member of the fictional boy group SHAX.
